                  <persName id="t18290409-212-person2008">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SINCLAIR
               <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2008" type="surname" value="SINCLAIR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2008" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2008" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290409-212-viclabel1202" type="occupation">discharged soldier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-212-victim2007 t18290409-212-viclabel1202"></join>. On the 12th of March, I gave the prisoner a 5l. Bank note to fetch me change at the Commercial tap, as I did not know the value of change so well - I had known him about a month; he and I slept in the same room - he brought me no change, but I saw him next morning, between eight and nine o'clock; I asked him for the note or the change - he denied having had it; the number of the note begins with a 2; I am not a scholar, but I think there are four more figures.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-212-person2009">
                  SARAH 
                  WHITELOW
               <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2009" type="surname" value="WHITELOW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2009" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2009" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant at the Commercial inn; I gave the prisoner five sovereigns for a 5l. note - he said it was for a person whom he lodged with.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-212-person2010">
                  JAMES 
                  GILLMAN
               <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2010" type="surname" value="GILLMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2010" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-212-person2010" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner; he said he had no note from the prosecutor, but he had it from Mrs. Brotherington; I went there, and she said she did not give it him - the prisoner then said he had it from a gentleman, but he did not know where he lived; 3s. 4 1/2d. were found upon him - this is the note; it is number 29,950.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was quite intoxicated, and I do not recollect taking any note to get change.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 18.</p>
